        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", &c.] Probably the chief captain knew nothing of what St Paul had been saying, and would be surprised at the outbreak of rage on the part of the people, and conclude from it that there was some serious charge laid against him which he might best ascertain by subjecting his prisoner to torture till he should confess.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
